Standard Security Life Insurance Company
                          of New York

                      Standard Security Life is licensed in all 50 states. The company is rated A- (Excellent) for financial 
                      strength by the A.M. Best Company Inc., a widely recognized rating agency that rates insurance companies 
                      on their relative financial strength and ability to meet policyholder obligations (An A++ rating from A.M.
                      Best is its highest rating)
                  

Madison National Life Insurance
                          Company, Inc.

                      Madison National Life is licensed in 49 states and specializes in health, life and
                      disability insurance. The company is rated A- (Excellent) for financial strength by the A.M. Best Company Inc.
                  

Independence American
                          Insurance Company

                      Independence American is licensed in all 50 states and its products include short-term medical, hospital indemnity, 
                      fixed indemnity limited benefit, group and individual dental, and pet insurance. 
                      The company is rated A- (Excellent) for financial strength by the A.M. Best Company Inc.
                      
                  

                      A.M. Best’s Rating Report

• Standard Security Life Insurance Company of New York
• Madison National Life Insurance Company, Inc.
• Independence American Insurance Company


                      IHC Specialty Benefits, Inc.

                      IHC Specialty Benefits, Inc., is a full-service marketing and distribution company that 
                      focuses on individual, consumer and small employer products. Products are marketed through 
                      general agents, online, telebrokerage, advisor centers, private label and directly to consumers. 
                      The company conducts business under the following brands:
                      
• HealtheDeals.com

                                A website which provides information for individuals  who want to learn more about their 
                                health insurance options and shop for coverage online or through the Health eDeals Call Center. 
                                Health eDeals also provides a referral service, Agent Finder, for consumers who wish to work 
                                with an advisor in their area.
                            

• Health eDeals Advisors

                                A national marketing organization that distributes major medical insurance plans, as well as other 
                                health insurance plans and health membership programs. Also includes a telesales marketing company 
                                consisting of licensed health insurance agents responsible for assisting consumers with the online 
                                purchasing process of The IHC Group portfolio of products.
                            

• Aspira A Mas

                              Aspira A Más is a sales and marketing division that is dedicated to serving the Hispanic 
                              community with a focus on health insurance education as well as providing affordable 
                              insurance products. Products are marketed through general agents, online and advisors. 
                          
• PetPlace

                              Published since 1999, PetPlace.com is the popular and trusted internet destination for pet 
                              parents concerned about their pet’s health and well-being. The site provides 10,000+ vet 
                              approved articles and other useful content to over 1,000,000 visitors per month. PetPlace 
                              sits at the hub of IHC’s Pet Health Division which brings pet insurance solutions to the 
                              market through D2C online outlets, agents, and strategic partners.
                          


Healthinsurance.org, LLC 


                      Published since 1994, healthinsurance.org™ is the Internet's oldest, most-trusted
                      independent site offering consumer information on affordable health and medical
                      coverage. Healthinsurance.org has worked hard to earn consumers' respect and loyalty.
                      The information it presents is intended for a general consumer audience.
                  

PetPartners Inc.


                      PetPartners provides pet health insurance in all 50 states of the United States, offering products to individuals 
                      and groups (such as associations, companies and credit unions). Since 2002, PetPartners has been the exclusive provider 
                      of pet health insurance protection to registrants of the American Kennel Club through the AKC Pet Insurance brand. 
                      In 2004, PetPartners was selected by the Cat Fanciers' Association, the largest registry of purebred cats, to provide 
                      health insurance to CFA registrants. Founded by Sir John D. Spurling, a leading British innovator in pet insurance who 
                      remains on its Board of Directors, PetPartners became a member of The IHC Group in 2017.
                  

                      IHC Carrier Solutions, Inc.

                      IHC Carrier Solutions is a program management, actuarial and regulatory compliance
                      firm providing product and business development, valuation services and business
                      block evaluation for IHC’s fully insured health segment.
                  
 Cook & Company Insurance Services, Inc.
 
                    Founded in 1981, Cook & Company Insurance Services, Inc. specializes in the 
                    Massachusetts municipal market by helping cities and towns control the cost of 
                    insurance and mitigate risk by providing health plan consulting services,  
                    Workers’ Compensation administration (also available to private sector businesses), 
                    reinsurance brokerage, claims recovery programs and special risk insurance called Injury on Duty (IOD). 
                



