Independence Holding Company Key Developments

Independence Holding Company Announces Declaration of Semi-Annual Cash Dividend, Payment on July 31, 2017
Jul 5 17
Independence Holding Company reported declaration of semi-annual cash dividend of $0.06 per share of common stock, payable to stockholders of record on July 17, 2017, with a payment date of July 31, 2017.


Independence Holding Company Announces Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
Jun 16 17
Independence Holding Company announced consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported revenue was $71,840,000 against $75,895,000 a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $7,547,000 against $9,472,000 a year ago. Income from continuing operations, net of tax was $5,009,000 against $5,896,000 a year ago. Net income was $5,009,000 against $115,666,000 a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was $4,936,000 against $106,010,000 a year ago. Diluted income per common share from continuing operations was $0.29 against $0.33 a year ago. Diluted income per common share was $0.29 against $6.08 a year ago. Revenues decreased primarily due to a reduction in premiums from the 100% co-insurance of the company's stop-loss business produced by Risk Solutions.


Independence Holding Company Reports Consolidated Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended December 31, 2016
May 22 17
Independence Holding Company reported consolidated earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year ended December 31, 2016. For the quarter, the company's revenues were $78,871,000 compared with $124,602,000 a year ago. Revenues decreased primarily due to a reduction in premiums from the 100% co-insurance of the company's stop-loss business produced by Risk Solutions. Income from continuing operations, net of tax was $7,753,000 against $3,892,000 for the same period prior year. Net income was $8,645,000 against $5,147,000 for the same period prior year. Net income attributable to the company was $8,529,000 against $4,933,000 for the same period prior year. Basic income per common share was $0.50 against $0.29 for the same period prior year. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $8,742,000 compared to $6,197,000 a year ago. Diluted net income per share from continuing operations was $0.44 compared to $0.21 a year ago. Diluted income per common share was $0.49, up from $0.28 in the year-ago period.

For the full year, the company's revenues were $311,004,000 compared with $530.5 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations, net of tax was $22,510,000 against $27,974,000 for the same period prior year. Net income was $133,314,000 against $30,522,000 for the same period prior year. Net income attributable to the company was $123,298,000 against $29,944,000 for the same period prior year. Diluted income per common share from continuing operations was $1.27 against $1.58 for the same period prior year. Diluted income per common share was $7.09 against $1.71 for the same period prior year. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $32,065,000 compared to $43,878,000 a year ago. Diluted income per common share from continuing operations of $1.27 compared to $1.58 a year ago.


